# Operating-Volume-Engineering — .gitignore
#
# What this file does:
#   - Excludes OS / editor / AI-tooling junk that should never be committed
#   - Excludes operator-private environment + secrets files
#   - Excludes the operator's _USER.md and per-cartridge design-state by default
#     (Convention 8 — Operator-Private Zone)
#   - DOES NOT exclude any engine, template, prototype, or meta content
#   - DOES NOT exclude the five shipped worked-example cartridges (Convention 8
#     Shipped Examples Zone — overrides re-include them at the bottom)

# ============================================================
# Mac filesystem metadata
# ============================================================
.DS_Store
**/.DS_Store
._*
.Spotlight-V100
.Trashes

# ============================================================
# Editor / IDE artifacts
# ============================================================
.vscode/
*.code-workspace
.idea/
*.iml
*.iws
*.swp
*.swo
*.swn
*~
.netrwhist
\#*\#
.\#*
*.sublime-workspace
*.sublime-project

# ============================================================
# Obsidian workspace state (user-specific UI)
# ============================================================
.obsidian/workspace*
.obsidian/cache
.obsidian/graph.json
.obsidian/workspace-mobile.json
.obsidian/workspaces.json

# ============================================================
# OS / network artifacts
# ============================================================
Thumbs.db
.directory
ehthumbs.db
desktop.ini
$RECYCLE.BIN/

# ============================================================
# AI tooling state (Claude Code, Cursor, etc.)
# ============================================================
.claude/
.claude.json
.cursor/
.copilot/
.ai-cache/
.chatcache/

# ============================================================
# Environment + secrets
# ============================================================
.env
.env.local
.env.*.local
.envrc
*.pem
*.key
*.p12
*.pfx
credentials.json
secrets.yaml
secrets.yml
*.secret

# ============================================================
# Backup + temporary files
# ============================================================
*.bak
*.backup
*.orig
*.tmp
*.temp

# ============================================================
# Log files
# ============================================================
*.log
logs/
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*

# ============================================================
# Archive + compressed files
# ============================================================
*.zip
*.tar
*.tar.gz
*.tgz
*.rar
*.7z

# ============================================================
# Language runtimes (in case the operator runs scripts alongside OVE)
# ============================================================
# Python
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
*.egg-info/
.venv/
venv/

# Node
node_modules/
.npm/

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------
# Personal design work — excluded by default so this folder can be shared
# without leaking active design conversations.
#
# TRADE-OFF: the OV's core thesis is "state lives in files." Excluding
# _design-state.md and Sessions/*.md by default means YOUR own design
# history is NOT version-controlled unless you opt in. To track your own
# cartridge, see INSTALL.md § "Tracking your own design history" — there
# is a copy-paste `git add -f` recipe there. Edit this section to flip
# the default if you'd rather track-by-default.
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------

# Design-state files: live record of where each design engagement stands
**/_design-state.md

# Optional user profile (Convention 8 — Operator-Private Zone; never auto-inferred
# per P7 / F3 identity rule — the populated _USER.md stays local; only the
# _USER.md.template ships)
_USER.md

# Personal cartridges — exclude session content and decision logs by default.
# To track your own cartridge, use `git add -f` on the specific paths.
**/Sessions/*.md
!**/Sessions/.gitkeep

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------
# Always tracked (overrides above for the shipped worked examples):
# The five shipped cartridges demonstrate the system and their contents
# are part of the release.
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------
!SOLVE-eX-Retrospective/**
!LifeLong-Learning-Retrospective/**
!Negotiation-Preparation/**
!Long-Form-Writing/**
!Relationship-Cultivation/**
!Political-Landscape-Cartography-Retrospective/**
